outcomes.title: Asymptotes and End Behavior
outcomes.description: Verify vertical asymptotes and determine end behavior and horizonatal asymptotes.
outcomes.template:
Consider the function f(x):

f(x) = {{fx}}

Task 1: Vertical Asymptote Verification

Verify whether the vertical line x={{a}} is a vertical asymptote of f(x) by evaluating the following one-sided limits. Explain your reasoning.

Task 2: End Behavior and Horizontal Asymptotes

Determine the end behavior of f(x) by evaluating the limits at infinity. State the equation(s) of any horizontal asymptotes (or state that none exist).

Summary of Results

Task 1 Limits:
\lim_{x \to {{a}}^+} f(x) = {{lim_plus}}
\lim_{x \to {{a}}^-} f(x) = {{lim_minus}}

Task 1 Conclusion: Is x={{a}} a vertical asymptote? {{#is_va_at_a}} \text{Yes} {{/is_va_at_a}} {{^is_va_at_a}} \text{No} {{/is_va_at_a}}
(Note: A VA occurs if either one-sided limit is $\pm\infty$.)

Task 2 Limits:
\lim_{x \to \infty} f(x) = {{lim_inf_plus}}
\lim_{x \to -\infty} f(x) = {{lim_inf_minus}}

Task 2 Conclusion: Horizontal Asymptote(s) Equation(s): {{ha_equation}}
